    "---\n",
    "## 🌡 2.5.2: The Temperature Scaler Math\n",
    "\n",
    "Temperature ($T > 0$) scales logits before they are fed into Softmax. It acts as an entropy controller:\n",
    "$$z'_i = \\frac{z_i}{T}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "- Setting $T > 1$ flattens the distribution (increasing entropy, making responses more creative/random).\n",
    "- Setting $T \\to 0$ spikes the highest logit towards $1.0$ and others to $0.0$ (greedy, highly deterministic deterministic choices)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# TODO: Implement temperature-scaled softmax.\n",
    "def scaled_softmax(logits: List[float], temperature: float) -> List[float]:\n",
    "    # Scale each logit by temperature, then compute softmax\n",
    "    scaled_logits = [z / temperature for z in logits]\n",
    "    return softmax(scaled_logits)\n",
    "\n",
    "raw_scores = [2.0, 1.0, 0.5]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Try high temperature (Creative)\n",
    "creative_probs = scaled_softmax(raw_scores, 2.0)\n",
    "print(f\"Creative (T=2.0): {creative_probs}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Try low temperature (Deterministic)\n",
    "deterministic_probs = scaled_softmax(raw_scores, 0.1)\n",
    "print(f\"Deterministic (T=0.1): {deterministic_probs}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "assert creative_probs[0] < deterministic_probs[0], \"Low temperature should spike the top probability\"\n",
    "print(\"Success! Temperature scaling mastered.\")"
   ]
